Na$_{2}$Ti$_{3}$Cl$_{8}$ can be found in three different phases (H\"{a}nni, 2017): \begin{itemize} \item $\gamma$-Na$_{2}$Ti$_{3}$Cl$_{8}$, below 210K (heating) or 190K (cooling) (this structure). \item $\beta$-Na$_{2}$Ti$_{3}$Cl$_{8}$ is found between 190 and 210K when samples are cooled.  It is in the $R\overline{3}m$ space group, but we have no atomic positions. \item $\alpha$-Na$_{2}$Ti$_{3}$Cl$_{8}$, above 190/210K, is in the \href{current_web_home_dir/A8B3C2_hR13_166_ch_e_c-001}{Na$_{2}$Mn$_{3}$Cl$_{8}$ structure}. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 (H\"{a}nni, 2017) give the lattice constants of $\gamma$-Na$_{2}$Ti$_{3}$Cl$_{8}$ at 2K, and the atomic positions at 1.6K. 
 Hexagonal settings of this structure can be obtained with the option {\tt --hex}.
